# Incident Title: DNS Resolution Failure

## 1. Summary
Multiple users reported being unable to access the website due to DNS resolution failure.

## 2. Detection
The incident was detected after customer complaints and confirmed by IT using network traffic analysis.

## 3. Analysis
- Protocol: UDP
- Service: DNS
- Port: 53
- Error Observed: ICMP "Port Unreachable"
- Tool Used: tcpdump

## 4. Root Cause
The DNS server was not responding on UDP port 53, likely due to a firewall misconfiguration or DNS service outage.

## 5. Impact
Users were unable to access the website, causing service disruption.

## 6. Mitigation & Recovery
- Verified DNS service status
- Reviewed firewall rules
- Restored DNS functionality

## 7. Lessons Learned
- Importance of DNS monitoring
- Firewall rule validation
- Early detection through log analysis

## 8. Confidence Level
Medium â€“ Further confirmation required via firewall and DNS server logs.

Evidence Collected:
- tcpdump DNS traffic logs
- ICMP "udp port 53 unreachable" messages
- Source IPs and timestamps observed
